270
00:13:18,101 --> 00:13:19,363
Um hmm.

271
00:13:19,407 --> 00:13:22,323
And once his meal ticket
dried up, he was gone.

272
00:13:22,366 --> 00:13:23,454
Just like I said he'd be.

273
00:13:23,498 --> 00:13:25,108
I know that too.

274
00:13:25,152 --> 00:13:26,216
I was there through it all.

275
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,241
Remember?

276
00:13:27,981 --> 00:13:29,286
I know.

277
00:13:29,330 --> 00:13:31,462
You were a faithful manager
and friend.

278
00:13:32,768 --> 00:13:34,465
But if we do this again

279
00:13:34,509 --> 00:13:36,598
it's got to be different.

280
00:13:36,641 --> 00:13:38,078
ASHLYN: You can say that again.

281
00:13:38,121 --> 00:13:41,124
Oh, I love that we agree
on something.

282
00:13:42,517 --> 00:13:44,867
I didn't give ya a proper
hello last night.

283
00:13:44,911 --> 00:13:45,868
ASHLYN: Hey Bret.

284
00:13:45,912 --> 00:13:46,869
Good to see ya.

285
00:13:46,913 --> 00:13:47,957
You too.

286
00:13:48,001 --> 00:13:50,264
Okay ladies, to your corners.

287
00:13:56,618 --> 00:13:59,969
So, have you given some thought
to the proposal?

288
00:14:00,013 --> 00:14:02,232
Question, what exactly do they
want for this offer?

289
00:14:02,276 --> 00:14:03,625
A Christmas EP.

290
00:14:03,668 --> 00:14:06,019
Two classic Christmas songs
and one original.

291
00:14:06,062 --> 00:14:07,411
A new one?

292
00:14:07,455 --> 00:14:09,761
This says we only have
a few weeks.

293
00:14:09,805 --> 00:14:11,154
Yep.

294
00:14:11,198 --> 00:14:13,113
They want to release the songs
on Christmas Eve.

295
00:14:14,766 --> 00:14:15,898
[Bonnie sighs]

296
00:14:15,942 --> 00:14:17,552
I think it's a great offer.

297
00:14:17,595 --> 00:14:21,469
Especially considering your
illustrious solo careers.

298
00:14:21,512 --> 00:14:22,513
Oh!

299
00:14:24,515 --> 00:14:25,473
Okay fine.

300
00:14:25,516 --> 00:14:26,691
I'll do it.

301
00:14:26,735 --> 00:14:28,650
But then I go my way.

302
00:14:30,478 --> 00:14:31,566
And I go mine.

303
00:14:32,393 --> 00:14:33,655
Great.

304
00:14:33,698 --> 00:14:35,067
So I've lined you up with
Smith Carter.

305
00:14:35,091 --> 00:14:36,721
He's the hottest producer in
the industry right now.

306
00:14:36,745 --> 00:14:38,027
I've also got you a photo shoot
for the promo kit

307
00:14:38,051 --> 00:14:39,487
and a one to one interview.

308
00:14:40,967 --> 00:14:41,924
Wow.

309
00:14:41,968 --> 00:14:43,534
That didn't take long.

310
00:14:43,578 --> 00:14:45,710
I might be grayer but I can
still make things happen.

311
00:14:46,973 --> 00:14:49,279
Well I think you look
distinguished.

312
00:14:49,323 --> 00:14:50,324
Thank you.

313
00:14:51,412 --> 00:14:52,717
Um hmm.

314
00:14:52,761 --> 00:14:55,111
[happy music]

315
00:15:10,257 --> 00:15:11,780
You must be Smith.

316
00:15:11,823 --> 00:15:12,955
Ms. Rose.

317
00:15:12,999 --> 00:15:14,739
It's really great to meet you.

318
00:15:14,783 --> 00:15:16,587
Looking forward to digging
into this with the both of you.

319
00:15:16,611 --> 00:15:17,960
Cool, great.

320
00:15:18,004 --> 00:15:19,005
ASHLYN: Mother.

321
00:15:19,875 --> 00:15:21,485
Ashlyn.

322
00:15:21,529 --> 00:15:24,184
Riley, I'm so glad you came!

323
00:15:24,227 --> 00:15:25,228
I'm Smith.

324
00:15:26,186 --> 00:15:27,752
Hi, I'm...

325
00:15:27,796 --> 00:15:29,232
The Ashlyn Rose.

326
00:15:30,668 --> 00:15:33,106
I dropped the "the" years ago.

327
00:15:33,149 --> 00:15:34,977
This is my daughter Riley.

328
00:15:35,021 --> 00:15:36,239
Hey.

329
00:15:36,283 --> 00:15:37,937
You're here to keep these
two in line?

330
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:40,809
I do what I can but I make
no promises.

331
00:15:40,852 --> 00:15:42,158
[all chuckling]

332
00:15:42,202 --> 00:15:43,657
So what do you have planned
for your original?

333
00:15:43,681 --> 00:15:46,858
I can only imagine what you have
after all this time.

334
00:15:46,902 --> 00:15:50,079
We don't actually have anything
written yet.

335
00:15:51,863 --> 00:15:52,952
Oh, okay.

336
00:15:52,995 --> 00:15:54,779
Then let's tackle the
other two songs.

337
00:15:54,823 --> 00:15:56,433
What classics have you chosen?

338
00:15:57,304 --> 00:15:59,567
Well, we haven't, yet.

339
00:16:00,742 --> 00:16:03,527
We could always do
"Little Drummer Boy".

340
00:16:03,571 --> 00:16:06,704
[sighs] That's been done
to death.

341
00:16:06,748 --> 00:16:09,229
Then by all means, why
don't you choose.

342
00:16:09,272 --> 00:16:11,492
Smith, would you please put
us out of our misery

343
00:16:11,535 --> 00:16:13,015
and choose a song?

344
00:16:13,059 --> 00:16:15,452
Anything but the
"Little Drummer Boy".

345
00:16:15,496 --> 00:16:18,629
Okay, how 'bout
"Hark the Herald Angels Sing"?

346
00:16:18,673 --> 00:16:20,675
Been working on a more modern,
upbeat version

347
00:16:20,718 --> 00:16:22,155
that I think you might like.

348
00:16:22,198 --> 00:16:24,809
I've got a rough instrumentation
to use as a guide track.

349
00:16:24,853 --> 00:16:27,160
If you wanna hear it?

350
00:16:27,203 --> 00:16:28,988
- Let's do it.
- Cool.

351
00:16:29,031 --> 00:16:29,989
[Bonnie chuckles]

352
00:16:30,032 --> 00:16:31,032
BONNIE: Let's go.

353
00:16:33,862 --> 00:16:34,906
Here it comes.

354
00:16:36,212 --> 00:16:38,693
[bright music]

355
00:16:43,828 --> 00:16:44,960
Do you wanna take that?

356
00:16:45,004 --> 00:16:45,961
- Yeah.
- Then I'll take?

357
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:46,962
Then I'll go?

358
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:47,963
- Yep.
- Okay.

359
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,008
All right, we can go.

360
00:16:50,792 --> 00:16:53,490
[bright music]

361
00:16:59,322 --> 00:17:03,979
♪ Hark the herald angels sing

362
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:08,462
♪ Glory to the newborn king

363
00:17:08,505 --> 00:17:12,944
♪ Peace on Earth and
mercy mild ♪

364
00:17:12,988 --> 00:17:17,732
♪ God and sinners reconciled

365
00:17:17,775 --> 00:17:21,823
♪ Joyful all ye nations rise

366
00:17:21,866 --> 00:17:26,393
♪ Join the triumph of
the skies ♪

367
00:17:26,436 --> 00:17:30,701
♪ With angelic hosts proclaim

368
00:17:30,745 --> 00:17:35,315
♪ Christ is born in Bethlehem

369
00:17:35,358 --> 00:17:40,363
♪ Hark the herald angels sing

370
00:17:41,234 --> 00:17:45,238
♪ Glory to the newborn king

371
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:54,073
Yeah?

372
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:04,779
[applauding]

373
00:18:04,822 --> 00:18:07,303
That was amazing.

374
00:18:07,347 --> 00:18:09,871
It's okay, you can be happy.

375
00:18:11,002 --> 00:18:12,700
I'm just happy you're happy,
sweetheart.

376
00:18:12,743 --> 00:18:13,701
Any notes?

377
00:18:13,744 --> 00:18:14,702
No.

378
00:18:14,745 --> 00:18:16,138
That was perfect.

379
00:18:16,182 --> 00:18:17,681
Let's call it a day while I play
around with the mix.

380
00:18:17,705 --> 00:18:19,489
Meanwhile you both can figure
out

381
00:18:19,533 --> 00:18:20,925
the next song you wanna do.

382
00:18:20,969 --> 00:18:22,362
Sounds good.

383
00:18:22,405 --> 00:18:24,973
And Ashlyn, I was hoping you'd
come in another time

384
00:18:25,016 --> 00:18:26,279
to lay down some guitar.

385
00:18:26,322 --> 00:18:29,412
I'm gonna add a second guitar
to make it pop.

386
00:18:29,456 --> 00:18:31,893
I was thinking maybe something
like this.

387
00:18:36,811 --> 00:18:40,031
[bright guitar music]

388
00:18:54,524 --> 00:18:56,396
That was great.

389
00:18:56,439 --> 00:18:57,745
Yeah, really something.

390
00:18:57,788 --> 00:18:59,399
But you know, we oughta
get going

391
00:18:59,442 --> 00:19:00,965
because we've got a
lotta work to do

392
00:19:01,009 --> 00:19:03,925
and we gotta get up early for an
interview in the morning.

393
00:19:03,968 --> 00:19:05,448
So.

394
00:19:05,492 --> 00:19:08,625
Hey Riley, we should talk
about [whispers].

395
00:19:12,629 --> 00:19:15,154
It was really great to
meet you, Smith.

396
00:19:16,024 --> 00:19:17,068
You too.

397
00:19:17,852 --> 00:19:20,594
[gentle music]

398
00:19:23,292 --> 00:19:24,815
So the studio and the
upcoming tour

399
00:19:24,859 --> 00:19:26,077
that we're looking forward to.

400
00:19:26,121 --> 00:19:26,904
I mean there's a lot coming
down the pike.

401
00:19:26,948 --> 00:19:27,905
Stick to the music.

402
00:19:27,949 --> 00:19:29,559
Personal lives off limits.

403
00:19:29,603 --> 00:19:30,604
Agreed.

404
00:19:30,647 --> 00:19:32,171
And here they are.

405
00:19:32,214 --> 00:19:33,172
The Roses.

406
00:19:33,215 --> 00:19:34,216
BONNIE AND ASHLYN: Hi.

407
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:35,217
- Ashyln.
- Nice to meet you.

408
00:19:35,261 --> 00:19:36,436
Hi there, I'm Bonnie.

409
00:19:36,479 --> 00:19:38,655
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you too.

410
00:19:38,699 --> 00:19:39,917
Let's get right into it.

411
00:19:39,961 --> 00:19:41,267
ASHLYN: Okay.

412
00:19:41,310 --> 00:19:43,399
How does it feel seeing how
popular the video

413
00:19:43,443 --> 00:19:44,879
of your performance was?

414
00:19:44,922 --> 00:19:47,011
I think we were both a
little shocked.

415
00:19:47,055 --> 00:19:48,926
Yes, I don't think we realized

416
00:19:48,970 --> 00:19:52,843
how loyal our fans were after
all these years.

417
00:19:52,887 --> 00:19:54,149
We were very touched.

418
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:56,891
It must feel great being back
in the studio

419
00:19:56,934 --> 00:19:58,327
and recording.

420
00:19:58,371 --> 00:20:01,591
Well there is no place
I'd rather be, honestly.

421
00:20:01,635 --> 00:20:03,463
It's like we never stopped.

422
00:20:03,506 --> 00:20:04,899
Yes.

423
00:20:04,942 --> 00:20:06,422
But you did stop.

424
00:20:06,466 --> 00:20:09,033
For about 15 years when
you both pursued

425
00:20:09,077 --> 00:20:12,298
rather disappointing solo
careers.

426
00:20:12,341 --> 00:20:14,952
Is that what brought you back
together as a duo?

427
00:20:14,996 --> 00:20:18,304
Well our retirement was
pretty public.

428
00:20:18,347 --> 00:20:21,872
So it just felt right for the
Roses to come back.

429
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:23,134
Um hmm.

430
00:20:23,178 --> 00:20:24,547
Bonnie, how do you reconcile
with the fact

431
00:20:24,571 --> 00:20:27,051
that Ashlyn walked away
from the Roses

432
00:20:27,095 --> 00:20:29,706
and broke up the band?

433
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:33,014
Well we try not to dwell
on the past.

434
00:20:33,057 --> 00:20:35,016
I mean it was tough,
but that was then.

435
00:20:35,059 --> 00:20:36,017
Hmm.

436
00:20:36,060 --> 00:20:37,627
Ashlyn, your mom can be quoted

437
00:20:37,671 --> 00:20:42,110
saying that she didn't like Beau
Niland, your ex-husband.

438
00:20:42,937 --> 00:20:43,938
Thank you.

439
00:20:43,981 --> 00:20:45,418
I know who Beau Niland is.

440
00:20:45,461 --> 00:20:48,290
She called you silly,
young and impulsive.

441
00:20:48,334 --> 00:20:50,945
Have you worked through those
differences?

442
00:20:50,988 --> 00:20:54,905
Well you know, mothers always
think they know best.

443
00:20:54,949 --> 00:20:55,950
And sometimes they do.

444
00:20:55,993 --> 00:20:57,386
Yeah and as a daughter,

445
00:20:57,430 --> 00:21:00,041
you just really want your mother
to be there for you

446
00:21:00,084 --> 00:21:02,086
and it's disappointing when
she's not.

447
00:21:02,130 --> 00:21:03,958
And it's painful you know,

448
00:21:04,001 --> 00:21:05,873
when you hear through the press

449
00:21:05,916 --> 00:21:07,091
of your daughter's engagement

450
00:21:07,135 --> 00:21:10,225
and subsequent departure from
the band.

451
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:11,400
Hmm.

452
00:21:11,444 --> 00:21:14,838
How will it be different
this time?

453
00:21:14,882 --> 00:21:17,319
Okay, I thank you for
your questions.

454
00:21:17,363 --> 00:21:19,278
It looks like you got what
you came for.

455
00:21:19,321 --> 00:21:20,429
We're on a very tight deadline

456
00:21:20,453 --> 00:21:21,691
and the Roses need to practice.

457
00:21:21,715 --> 00:21:23,238
Are you guys dating anyone?

458
00:21:26,589 --> 00:21:27,634
Did you get all that?

459
00:21:32,029 --> 00:21:33,640
Well that was a disaster.

460
00:21:33,683 --> 00:21:35,250
And yet I'm not surprised
at all.

461
00:21:35,294 --> 00:21:38,427
You could've controlled yourself
a little more, Ashlyn.

462
00:21:38,471 --> 00:21:41,343
Oh, so now you're blaming
me, again.

463
00:21:41,387 --> 00:21:43,040
You never wanna hear the truth.

464
00:21:43,084 --> 00:21:45,478
Not about Beau, not about
yourself.

465
00:21:45,521 --> 00:21:48,089
Because you're such a great
judge of character, mother.

466
00:21:48,132 --> 00:21:50,352
Hey, we can work through this.

467
00:21:50,396 --> 00:21:52,615
No press is bad press, right?

468
00:21:52,659 --> 00:21:53,877
ASHYLN: No thanks.

469
00:21:53,921 --> 00:21:56,271
This was never going to
work, Bret.

470
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:57,272
Yeah.

471
00:21:57,316 --> 00:21:58,516
At least we can agree on that.

472
00:21:59,405 --> 00:22:02,277
[thoughtful music]

473
00:22:17,423 --> 00:22:19,425
[sighs]

474
00:22:33,308 --> 00:22:35,571
BEAU: Hey, I'm probably
somewhere making music.

475
00:22:35,615 --> 00:22:36,833
Leave a message.

476
00:22:38,313 --> 00:22:41,490
Hey Beau, I'm sure you're off
living your best life.

477
00:22:41,534 --> 00:22:43,710
But could you please

478
00:22:43,753 --> 00:22:47,453
send the child support for our
daughter that she needs?

479
00:22:47,496 --> 00:22:49,106
So if you could send
the money ASAP

480
00:22:49,150 --> 00:22:51,195
that would be great.

481
00:22:51,239 --> 00:22:52,240
Thanks.

482
00:22:58,289 --> 00:23:00,248
[sighs]

483
00:23:10,345 --> 00:23:11,346
Riley.

484
00:23:12,478 --> 00:23:14,044
What's going on?

485
00:23:14,088 --> 00:23:15,568
Why couldn't you just get along?

486
00:23:16,786 --> 00:23:18,658
I barely started to
get to know her

487
00:23:18,701 --> 00:23:20,921
and you blow it up in one day.

488
00:23:20,964 --> 00:23:25,969
Riley, what happened between
your grandmother and I,

489
00:23:27,231 --> 00:23:28,407
there's a long history there

490
00:23:28,450 --> 00:23:29,514
and I don't know that things

491
00:23:29,538 --> 00:23:30,776
will ever be the same
between us.

492
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,323
I'm sorry.

493
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:36,240
So when you told me you would do
everything you could

494
00:23:36,284 --> 00:23:37,609
to get me what I wanted
for Christmas,

495
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:40,244
you meant only if it was
cheap and easy?

496
00:23:40,288 --> 00:23:43,813
No, Riley, these are grown
up problems

497
00:23:43,857 --> 00:23:47,164
and you are not privy to
all the details

498
00:23:47,208 --> 00:23:50,167
that made it not work
out between us.

499
00:23:50,211 --> 00:23:51,952
Didn't work out?

500
00:23:51,995 --> 00:23:54,128
Mom, me not getting the
part of Tiny Tim

501
00:23:54,171 --> 00:23:56,565
in the school Christmas play
didn't work out.

502
00:23:56,609 --> 00:23:57,566
This is way bigger.

503
00:23:57,610 --> 00:23:59,350
This is just you being stubborn.

504
00:24:02,615 --> 00:24:03,616
Riley, wait!

505
00:24:06,532 --> 00:24:08,447
[sighs]

506
00:24:16,890 --> 00:24:20,328
[door lock jangles]

507
00:24:20,371 --> 00:24:21,329
Riley come on.

508
00:24:21,372 --> 00:24:22,765
Please, you know the rules.

509
00:24:22,809 --> 00:24:24,201
No locked doors.

510
00:24:25,202 --> 00:24:26,552
Just leave me alone.

511
00:24:27,553 --> 00:24:29,946
[sad music]

512
00:24:47,050 --> 00:24:50,053
[soft guitar music]

513
00:24:58,540 --> 00:24:59,540
Hello?

514
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,283
Yeah.

515
00:25:02,326 --> 00:25:06,417
Hi, yes the guitar
is still available.

516
00:25:08,594 --> 00:25:11,510
Sure, 10 o'clock tomorrow works.

517
00:25:13,033 --> 00:25:14,904
6 Onetree Lane.

518
00:25:14,948 --> 00:25:17,124
[gasps] But I have dogs.

519
00:25:17,167 --> 00:25:18,299
Big dogs.

520
00:25:18,342 --> 00:25:19,422
I hope you're not allergic.

521
00:25:21,041 --> 00:25:22,216
Okay.

522
00:25:22,259 --> 00:25:23,304
No.

523
00:25:24,697 --> 00:25:27,395
No I cannot get Bonnie Rose
to sign the guitar.

524
00:25:27,438 --> 00:25:29,092
Ashyln is.

525
00:25:29,136 --> 00:25:30,529
Do you want the guitar or not?

526
00:25:32,182 --> 00:25:33,183
Great.

527
00:25:34,358 --> 00:25:35,359
See you tomorrow.

528
00:25:44,673 --> 00:25:46,675
[sighs]

529
00:25:50,331 --> 00:25:51,593
[doorbell rings]

530
00:25:51,637 --> 00:25:54,553
[thoughtful music]

531
00:26:01,690 --> 00:26:03,300
[sighs]

532
00:26:03,344 --> 00:26:05,912
Wow, you sure know how to make
a guy feel special.

533
00:26:05,955 --> 00:26:09,350
I'm sorry, I thought you might
be Ashlyn or Riley.

534
00:26:09,393 --> 00:26:10,786
Have you heard from either
of them?

535
00:26:10,830 --> 00:26:12,005
No, I have not.

536
00:26:12,048 --> 00:26:13,006
So I don't know what
to tell you.

537
00:26:13,049 --> 00:26:15,095
I guess the whole thing's off.

538
00:26:15,138 --> 00:26:18,664
Turns out time heals pretty much
nothing with that girl.

539
00:26:19,708 --> 00:26:21,449
Come in. Nope.

540
00:26:21,492 --> 00:26:22,537
Put your jacket on.

541
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:23,669
You're coming with me.

542
00:26:24,887 --> 00:26:27,281
Bret, would I go out at
this hour?

543
00:26:27,324 --> 00:26:29,413
'Cause you're not sitting around
brooding all night.

544
00:26:29,457 --> 00:26:30,632
I am taking you to dinner.

545
00:26:30,676 --> 00:26:31,633
Bret...

546
00:26:31,677 --> 00:26:32,765
I know you Bonnie Rose

547
00:26:32,808 --> 00:26:33,766
and I know being along in
this house

548
00:26:33,809 --> 00:26:34,941
is not doing you any good.

549
00:26:36,290 --> 00:26:37,508
It's Christmas time.

550
00:26:37,552 --> 00:26:38,509
Let's go enjoy it.

551
00:26:38,553 --> 00:26:39,554
Come on.

552
00:26:40,207 --> 00:26:41,164
[bright music]

553
00:26:41,208 --> 00:26:43,079
Let me get my jacket.

554
00:26:45,255 --> 00:26:46,363
I thought that bringing Ashlyn
back into your life

555
00:26:46,387 --> 00:26:48,781
would make ya happy again.

556
00:26:48,824 --> 00:26:50,106
I thought you two would find a
way to work things out,

557
00:26:50,130 --> 00:26:52,349
you know 'tis the season
and all.

558
00:26:52,393 --> 00:26:53,655
Um hmm.

559
00:26:53,699 --> 00:26:55,328
Well sometimes things can't
be worked out.

560
00:26:55,352 --> 00:26:57,137
They just gotta be worked
through.

561
00:26:57,180 --> 00:26:59,879
So how long before you reach
out this time?

562
00:26:59,922 --> 00:27:01,271
What?

563
00:27:01,315 --> 00:27:04,274
As far as I'm concerned,
the ball is in her court.

564
00:27:04,318 --> 00:27:05,754
How do ya figure?

565
00:27:05,798 --> 00:27:08,844
[sighs] Look, I can't
do this again.

566
00:27:08,888 --> 00:27:11,368
I mean all I did was
care for her.

567
00:27:11,412 --> 00:27:13,936
You know I mean I knew what
was best for her

568
00:27:13,980 --> 00:27:16,112
as her mother and her
business partner

569
00:27:16,156 --> 00:27:18,245
and I did the best I could.

570
00:27:18,288 --> 00:27:20,464
She picked the loser
and I'm the bad guy?

571
00:27:20,508 --> 00:27:22,292
No, I can't do it again.

572
00:27:22,336 --> 00:27:25,513
To be fair, you have picked a
loser too, as well.

573
00:27:27,558 --> 00:27:31,171
[laughs] You must think
the sun wakes up

574
00:27:31,214 --> 00:27:32,694
just to hear you crow.

575
00:27:32,738 --> 00:27:35,392
I'm just saying everyone makes
mistakes.

576
00:27:35,436 --> 00:27:37,612
Okay, well thank you wise one.

577
00:27:37,656 --> 00:27:38,831
Everyone makes mistakes.

578
00:27:38,874 --> 00:27:40,180
Let's drop it.

579
00:27:40,223 --> 00:27:41,964
♪ The herald angels sing

580
00:27:42,008 --> 00:27:45,446
Oh, you've gotta be kidding me.

581
00:27:45,489 --> 00:27:46,708
It's Christmas.

582
00:27:46,752 --> 00:27:48,318
Joy tends to lurk in
every corner.

583
00:27:48,362 --> 00:27:52,540
I'm about 10 seconds away
from a meltdown.

584
00:27:52,583 --> 00:27:56,196
♪ God and sinner reconciled

585
00:27:56,239 --> 00:28:00,243
♪ Joyful all ye nations rise

586
00:28:00,287 --> 00:28:01,786
Thank you, if you could keep
moving along,

587
00:28:01,810 --> 00:28:02,768
we'd appreciate it.

588
00:28:02,811 --> 00:28:04,073
Merry Christmas.

589
00:28:04,117 --> 00:28:05,422
- Merry Christmas.
- Thanks!

590
00:28:05,466 --> 00:28:06,946
That wasn't so hard, was it?

591
00:28:08,643 --> 00:28:10,340
I'm gonna need dessert.

592
00:28:10,384 --> 00:28:11,690
I'm gonna need more wine.

593
00:28:12,778 --> 00:28:14,475
Those carolers reminded me
of that time

594
00:28:14,518 --> 00:28:15,626
we got caught in the snowstorm

595
00:28:15,650 --> 00:28:17,521
after the Philadelphia show.

596
00:28:17,565 --> 00:28:18,740
- Oh yeah.
- Remember?

597
00:28:18,784 --> 00:28:20,152
It's like they appeared out
of nowhere,

598
00:28:20,176 --> 00:28:22,004
little Christmas angels who
kept us company

599
00:28:22,048 --> 00:28:23,614
until the snow plow came.

600
00:28:23,658 --> 00:28:25,616
Remember we called it snow jam?

601
00:28:25,660 --> 00:28:28,228
[laughing]

602
00:28:28,271 --> 00:28:29,533
Oh.

603
00:28:29,577 --> 00:28:31,057
Aw.

604
00:28:31,100 --> 00:28:33,581
You're a great man, Bret.

605
00:28:33,624 --> 00:28:34,625
You really are.

606
00:28:37,541 --> 00:28:38,586
Cheers.

607
00:28:42,068 --> 00:28:43,069
[doorbell rings]

608
00:28:45,245 --> 00:28:46,463
[sighs]

609
00:28:46,507 --> 00:28:47,464
Smith.

610
00:28:47,508 --> 00:28:50,554
I'm, I'm confused.

611
00:28:50,598 --> 00:28:52,252
Well this is awkward.

612
00:28:52,295 --> 00:28:53,969
I was given this address
to pick up a guitar

613
00:28:53,993 --> 00:28:55,516
that was once yours.

614
00:28:55,559 --> 00:28:56,735
Was that you?

615
00:28:56,778 --> 00:28:59,607
Well I guess better
you than a stranger.

616
00:28:59,650 --> 00:29:00,651
Come on in.

617
00:29:09,095 --> 00:29:11,184
Wow, I can't believe
you're selling Rosie.

618
00:29:15,057 --> 00:29:17,538
With all the artists
you've produced,

619
00:29:17,581 --> 00:29:19,322
what makes you want this guitar?

620
00:29:20,671 --> 00:29:25,676
[Smith sighs]
[gentle music]

621
00:29:26,590 --> 00:29:31,508
My mom, she was a huge
fan of the Roses.

622
00:29:32,596 --> 00:29:35,295
And I guess I was, am too.

623
00:29:36,644 --> 00:29:38,578
I figured it'd be a great
addition to my collection.

624
00:29:38,602 --> 00:29:41,475
Especially because we're
working together now.

625
00:29:41,518 --> 00:29:44,304
So, what's up?

626
00:29:45,522 --> 00:29:48,656
Well, sometimes
you have to let go

627
00:29:48,699 --> 00:29:51,441
of the things that you
love for the greater good.

628
00:29:51,485 --> 00:29:52,486
So.

629
00:29:54,401 --> 00:29:55,402
Wait.

630
00:29:56,533 --> 00:29:58,013
You can't.

631
00:29:58,057 --> 00:29:59,058
You're not ready.

632
00:30:02,713 --> 00:30:03,758
You're right.

633
00:30:04,715 --> 00:30:05,954
She's been with me from
the beginning.

634
00:30:05,978 --> 00:30:07,762
I'm sorry if you're in
a tough spot.

635
00:30:07,806 --> 00:30:10,504
I mean, if that's what it is.

636
00:30:10,547 --> 00:30:11,548
I'll figure it out.

637
00:30:12,985 --> 00:30:15,639
Just do me a favor,
don't tell anyone,

638
00:30:15,683 --> 00:30:17,728
especially not my mom.

639
00:30:17,772 --> 00:30:19,861
Yeah, of course.

640
00:30:19,905 --> 00:30:22,559
Yeah, I guess it's just fake
it 'til ya make it.

641
00:30:22,603 --> 00:30:25,606
And then fake it again
in my case.

642
00:30:26,694 --> 00:30:30,263
Ashlyn, there's nothing fake
about you.

643
00:30:30,306 --> 00:30:33,919
[soft guitar music]

644
00:30:33,962 --> 00:30:35,442
Is that Riley playing?

645
00:30:35,485 --> 00:30:36,443
Yeah.

646
00:30:36,486 --> 00:30:37,444
She plays a little.

647
00:30:37,487 --> 00:30:38,837
And she sings too.

648
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:39,880
Just like you.

649
00:30:40,664 --> 00:30:42,623
She's a really good kid.

650
00:30:42,666 --> 00:30:45,800
She just really wants
my mom around

651
00:30:45,844 --> 00:30:48,542
and I messed that up.

652
00:30:50,370 --> 00:30:51,632
That was over sharing.

653
00:30:51,675 --> 00:30:54,156
No, no, it's nice to see behind
the curtains.

654
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:55,592
Adds context to the art.

655
00:30:55,636 --> 00:30:57,483
I just wish I could do something
to help you both

656
00:30:57,507 --> 00:30:59,118
finish the record.

657
00:30:59,161 --> 00:31:00,859
I appreciate that.

658
00:31:00,902 --> 00:31:03,078
But when my mom digs
her heels in,

659
00:31:04,732 --> 00:31:06,865
you know that saying
wild horses.

660
00:31:09,041 --> 00:31:10,477
What?

661
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,000
Well it seems to me

662
00:31:12,044 --> 00:31:14,568
that maybe stubbornness runs
in the family.

663
00:31:16,570 --> 00:31:17,745
Maybe.

664
00:31:17,788 --> 00:31:19,573
So maybe it wouldn't be
so terrible

665
00:31:19,616 --> 00:31:21,053
if you gave it another try.

666
00:31:22,968 --> 00:31:24,230
Maybe.

667
00:31:24,273 --> 00:31:28,190
And maybe Riley would like
it if you did too.

668
00:31:28,234 --> 00:31:30,062
And so would I.

669
00:31:30,105 --> 00:31:31,715
All right, all right.

670
00:31:31,759 --> 00:31:32,803
I give.

671
00:31:32,847 --> 00:31:34,762
So I'll see you at the
studio then?

672
00:31:34,805 --> 00:31:35,806
Bring Rosie.

673
00:31:37,634 --> 00:31:39,375
ASHLYN: Thank you.

674
00:31:39,419 --> 00:31:40,637
Really.

675
00:31:40,681 --> 00:31:41,856
Just doing my job.

676
00:31:47,818 --> 00:31:49,864
[sighs]

677
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:52,649
[bright music]

678
00:32:24,638 --> 00:32:27,119
[beeping]

679
00:32:27,162 --> 00:32:31,732
♪ Silent night

680
00:32:31,775 --> 00:32:36,215
♪ Holy night

681
00:32:36,258 --> 00:32:40,567
♪ All is calm

682
00:32:40,610 --> 00:32:45,093
♪ All is bright

683
00:32:45,137 --> 00:32:49,706
♪ Round yon virgin

684
00:32:49,750 --> 00:32:54,189
♪ Mother and child

685
00:32:54,233 --> 00:32:57,714
♪ Holy infant

686
00:32:57,758 --> 00:33:02,719
♪ So tender and mild

687
00:33:03,894 --> 00:33:08,899
♪ Sleep in heavenly peace

688
00:33:16,820 --> 00:33:20,172
♪ Sleep in heavenly peace

689
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:38,103
Wow.

690
00:33:38,146 --> 00:33:40,279
You both still have it.

691
00:33:40,322 --> 00:33:42,300
It took me back to a special
place in my childhood.

692
00:33:42,324 --> 00:33:43,673
Was there ever a doubt?

693
00:33:43,717 --> 00:33:44,892
Mom!

694
00:33:44,935 --> 00:33:46,894
I'm just, I'm just kidding.

695
00:33:46,937 --> 00:33:49,114
I mean there was probably
legitimate doubts

696
00:33:49,157 --> 00:33:50,811
that we would even show
up today.

697
00:33:52,117 --> 00:33:53,292
It felt good out there.

698
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:55,424
It really did.

699
00:33:56,860 --> 00:33:58,220
We should talk about your
original.

700
00:33:58,253 --> 00:34:00,386
And considering the time
constraints,

701
00:34:00,429 --> 00:34:02,233
I took the liberty of writing
a little something

702
00:34:02,257 --> 00:34:04,912
that I hope you might like.

703
00:34:07,306 --> 00:34:08,698
Let's hear it.

704
00:34:12,311 --> 00:34:15,879
[energetic guitar music]

705
00:34:40,817 --> 00:34:43,603
Wow, that was amazing.

706
00:34:45,561 --> 00:34:48,782
I think I'm beginning to get in
the Christmas spirit.

707
00:34:50,044 --> 00:34:52,786
Yeah, you're quite the
talent, Smith.

708
00:34:52,829 --> 00:34:54,266
Glad you like it.

709
00:34:54,309 --> 00:34:56,244
So, let's try and get back in
the studio in a few days

710
00:34:56,268 --> 00:34:58,052
and we'll knock this outta
the park.

711
00:34:58,096 --> 00:35:01,403
Yeah, but in the meantime we
should get out of your hair

712
00:35:01,447 --> 00:35:05,886
so you can work your voodoo to
make us sound fabulous.

713
00:35:11,065 --> 00:35:12,632
SMITH: Hey Ashlyn.

714
00:35:12,675 --> 00:35:13,807
Yeah?

715
00:35:13,850 --> 00:35:15,896
Would you like to go
out tonight?

716
00:35:15,939 --> 00:35:19,117
Talk about guitars over dinner.

717
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:20,727
Oh wow.

718
00:35:22,424 --> 00:35:25,993
I would love to, but I have
to pick up Riley

719
00:35:26,036 --> 00:35:29,388
and then we do homework
and dinner.

720
00:35:29,431 --> 00:35:30,780
That sort of thing.

721
00:35:30,824 --> 00:35:32,347
Right.

722
00:35:32,391 --> 00:35:34,369
Well hey, maybe you could
come to a gig I have tomorrow.

723
00:35:34,393 --> 00:35:36,003
If you have time.

724
00:35:36,046 --> 00:35:38,745
I literally don't stay up
past 11 o'clock.

725
00:35:38,788 --> 00:35:40,573
It's the exciting life of a mom.

726
00:35:40,616 --> 00:35:43,010
Well it's at 3 o'clock.

727
00:35:43,053 --> 00:35:44,881
So you'll be home by dinner.

728
00:35:44,925 --> 00:35:48,102
Who has a gig at 3 o'clock
in the afternoon?

729
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:49,799
I do.

730
00:35:49,843 --> 00:35:51,888
So, I'll text you tomorrow.

731
00:35:51,932 --> 00:35:52,976
You in?

732
00:35:55,501 --> 00:35:56,502
Yeah.

733
00:35:58,373 --> 00:35:59,548
I would love to.

734
00:36:00,941 --> 00:36:01,942
Cool.

735
00:36:03,726 --> 00:36:04,858
See ya then.

736
00:36:32,929 --> 00:36:33,930
You made it.

737
00:36:33,974 --> 00:36:35,497
I did.

738
00:36:35,541 --> 00:36:38,718
This was not what I
was expecting.

739
00:36:38,761 --> 00:36:41,155
You look really beautiful.

740
00:36:42,852 --> 00:36:43,853
Thank you.

741
00:36:44,637 --> 00:36:45,681
Come with me.

742
00:36:45,725 --> 00:36:46,963
I got some people I want
you to meet.

743
00:36:46,987 --> 00:36:48,031
ASHLYN: Okay.

744
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:54,037
[chuckling]

745
00:36:57,780 --> 00:36:59,869
This is Karen and Michelle.

746
00:36:59,913 --> 00:37:01,088
You're in good hands.

747
00:37:01,131 --> 00:37:02,872
These two are my personal
body guards.

748
00:37:02,916 --> 00:37:05,266
Ladies, this is Ashlyn Rose.

749
00:37:05,310 --> 00:37:06,702
Nice to meet you both.

750
00:37:06,746 --> 00:37:08,095
I should get up there.

751
00:37:08,138 --> 00:37:09,899
Don't want them to start a
riot if I start late.

752
00:37:09,923 --> 00:37:11,664
Good luck.

753
00:37:11,707 --> 00:37:12,882
Hi.

754
00:37:12,926 --> 00:37:14,232
What's up everyone?

755
00:37:14,275 --> 00:37:17,235
[audience applauds]

756
00:37:20,238 --> 00:37:22,892
So I just wanna thank you guys
so much for having me back

757
00:37:22,936 --> 00:37:24,329
for our little Christmas
concert.

758
00:37:24,372 --> 00:37:27,114
You guys know how much I enjoy
spending time with you.

759
00:37:27,157 --> 00:37:28,681
[whistling]

760
00:37:28,724 --> 00:37:29,682
Carol!

761
00:37:29,725 --> 00:37:30,726
I know that was you.

762
00:37:30,770 --> 00:37:33,468
[crowd chuckles]

763
00:37:38,212 --> 00:37:41,433
♪ Up on the housetop reindeer
pause ♪

764
00:37:41,476 --> 00:37:44,174
♪ Out jumps old Santa Claus

765
00:37:44,218 --> 00:37:47,090
♪ Down the chimney with
lots of toys ♪

766
00:37:47,134 --> 00:37:52,139
♪ For all the little ones,
the Christmas joy ♪

767
00:37:54,315 --> 00:37:57,318
♪ And ho, ho, ho who
wouldn't go ♪

768
00:37:57,362 --> 00:38:00,147
♪ Ho, ho, ho who wouldn't go

769
00:38:00,190 --> 00:38:03,324
♪ Up on housetop click,
click, click ♪

770
00:38:03,368 --> 00:38:08,155
♪ Down the chimney with
old Saint Nick ♪

771
00:38:13,421 --> 00:38:16,424
[audience applauds]

772
00:38:21,560 --> 00:38:23,039
ASHLYN: That was amazing.

773
00:38:23,083 --> 00:38:26,173
And so incredibly sweet.

774
00:38:26,216 --> 00:38:28,044
Well, as the cliche goes I
get more out of it

775
00:38:28,088 --> 00:38:29,045
than they'll ever know.

776
00:38:29,089 --> 00:38:31,221
I have a million questions.

777
00:38:31,265 --> 00:38:33,354
Like what made you start
doing this?

778
00:38:34,399 --> 00:38:36,270
Well my grandma stayed there

779
00:38:36,314 --> 00:38:37,465
and it would always make
her so happy

780
00:38:37,489 --> 00:38:39,317
when I'd visit and play.

781
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:43,146
I loved seeing her lit up like
a Christmas tree.

782
00:38:43,190 --> 00:38:45,105
I just had to keep coming back.

783
00:38:45,148 --> 00:38:46,889
So you're the joy bringer.

784
00:38:46,933 --> 00:38:48,195
The joy bringer.

785
00:38:49,022 --> 00:38:50,066
I like that.

786
00:38:50,110 --> 00:38:51,416
[giggling]

787
00:38:51,459 --> 00:38:53,374
You know a lot of 'em don't
have any families

788
00:38:53,418 --> 00:38:55,071
or they've been forgotten about.

789
00:38:55,115 --> 00:38:57,117
So they go there for sense
of community.

790
00:38:57,944 --> 00:38:59,641
No one should be left alone.

791
00:38:59,685 --> 00:39:01,034
Especially on Christmas.

792
00:39:02,122 --> 00:39:03,253
Like my mother.

793
00:39:05,691 --> 00:39:08,258
I mean that's really special.

794
00:39:09,216 --> 00:39:10,391
And they love you.

795
00:39:10,435 --> 00:39:13,699
I mean they really love you.

796
00:39:13,742 --> 00:39:15,570
Yeah, especially Carol.

797
00:39:15,614 --> 00:39:18,747
Oh I felt more than one
set of eyes

798
00:39:18,791 --> 00:39:20,116
burning a hole in the
back of my head.

799
00:39:20,140 --> 00:39:22,229
I mean I feel lucky that I
just got outta there

800
00:39:22,272 --> 00:39:23,926
in one piece.

801
00:39:23,970 --> 00:39:26,364
So you must've always had a
musical Christmas then.

802
00:39:26,407 --> 00:39:28,148
We did.

803
00:39:28,191 --> 00:39:29,671
Back when I was 20, but my mom,

804
00:39:29,715 --> 00:39:32,370
she passed away unexpectedly.

805
00:39:33,545 --> 00:39:34,546
I'm so sorry.

806
00:39:35,460 --> 00:39:37,157
Thank you.

807
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:38,550
What was she like?

808
00:39:38,593 --> 00:39:40,595
Oh God, she was amazing.

809
00:39:40,639 --> 00:39:42,162
[chuckling]

810
00:39:42,205 --> 00:39:45,470
What resonates with me most is
just how selfless she was.

811
00:39:45,513 --> 00:39:46,949
She'd always remind me
to consider

812
00:39:46,993 --> 00:39:48,318
what the person next to me
