00:52:18,918 --> 00:52:19,919
Too soon.

1080
00:52:20,615 --> 00:52:22,226
Come on Riles.

1081
00:52:22,269 --> 00:52:24,271
We shouldn't have got into
it like that.

1082
00:52:29,233 --> 00:52:30,625
Riley come on.

1083
00:52:30,669 --> 00:52:31,931
Please, no locked doors.

1084
00:52:37,066 --> 00:52:38,067
I'm sorry.

1085
00:52:49,296 --> 00:52:50,950
[sighs]

1086
00:52:50,993 --> 00:52:53,431
[phone buzzes]

1087
00:52:56,216 --> 00:52:57,522
Hey Bret.

1088
00:52:57,565 --> 00:52:59,001
Hey to you.

1089
00:52:59,045 --> 00:53:01,090
Got the proofs back on
the photos.

1090
00:53:01,134 --> 00:53:02,179
They're incredible.

1091
00:53:03,223 --> 00:53:04,964
You and Ash have copies
in your inbox.

1092
00:53:06,139 --> 00:53:08,097
So many good ones we can use.

1093
00:53:08,141 --> 00:53:10,012
I even got a favorite.

1094
00:53:10,056 --> 00:53:11,251
- Listen.
- You see the chemistry

1095
00:53:11,275 --> 00:53:13,581
between you two in every shot.

1096
00:53:13,625 --> 00:53:16,280
It's nice seeing you guys
getting along so well.

1097
00:53:16,323 --> 00:53:18,934
- About that.
- What?

1098
00:53:18,978 --> 00:53:20,893
Oh please don't tell me there's
a problem.

1099
00:53:20,936 --> 00:53:23,243
[sighs] Well...

1100
00:53:23,287 --> 00:53:25,506
Christmas Eve is in three days.

1101
00:53:25,550 --> 00:53:26,507
What are you doing?

1102
00:53:26,551 --> 00:53:27,987
Are you available right now?

1103
00:53:28,030 --> 00:53:28,988
Don't answer that.

1104
00:53:29,031 --> 00:53:29,989
I'm coming over.

1105
00:53:30,032 --> 00:53:32,078
I... [phone beeps]

1106
00:53:32,121 --> 00:53:33,122
Bret?

1107
00:53:34,385 --> 00:53:36,387
[sighs]

1108
00:53:39,085 --> 00:53:41,087
What are you so happy about?

1109
00:53:41,130 --> 00:53:43,959
[playful music]

1110
00:53:52,316 --> 00:53:53,882
Okay Christmas angel,

1111
00:53:55,144 --> 00:53:57,799
could you please send me some
of your Christmas joy?

1112
00:54:00,149 --> 00:54:01,716
I sure could use it right now.

1113
00:54:22,171 --> 00:54:25,087
[knocking at door]

1114
00:54:27,002 --> 00:54:28,787
Tell me all about it.

1115
00:54:34,488 --> 00:54:35,924
We can fix this.

1116
00:54:48,110 --> 00:54:49,068
I don't know what to say.

1117
00:54:49,111 --> 00:54:51,940
I'm just really sorry.

1118
00:54:51,984 --> 00:54:52,985
[sighs]

1119
00:54:53,028 --> 00:54:54,900
We were doing so well.

1120
00:54:54,943 --> 00:54:58,164
I thought maybe we could get,
you know close again.

1121
00:54:58,207 --> 00:54:59,557
You both gave it a good effort.

1122
00:54:59,600 --> 00:55:02,211
Oh, she's just so stubborn.

1123
00:55:05,867 --> 00:55:06,868
What?

1124
00:55:08,217 --> 00:55:10,045
Now I want you to take this
with all the care

1125
00:55:10,089 --> 00:55:11,438
with which it is intended.

1126
00:55:13,353 --> 00:55:15,050
Spit it out.

1127
00:55:15,094 --> 00:55:17,052
Ashlyn is indeed a very
stubborn woman.

1128
00:55:17,096 --> 00:55:18,619
Well cheers to that.

1129
00:55:18,663 --> 00:55:19,838
And so are you.

1130
00:55:21,405 --> 00:55:23,929
- I beg your pardon?
- Oh come on, Bonnie.

1131
00:55:23,972 --> 00:55:24,973
You're two peas in a pod.

1132
00:55:25,017 --> 00:55:27,062
Even if the pod bursts apart.

1133
00:55:27,106 --> 00:55:29,040
Same stubborn thoughts that are
running through your head

1134
00:55:29,064 --> 00:55:30,544
are running through hers.

1135
00:55:39,292 --> 00:55:42,556
I have a question for you and
I want you to be honest.

1136
00:55:42,600 --> 00:55:44,602
More honest than I've been?

1137
00:55:44,645 --> 00:55:49,650
Well let's say as honest as
you've been so far.

1138
00:55:50,129 --> 00:55:51,173
Okay.

1139
00:55:52,653 --> 00:55:57,658
[sighs] Am I overbearing?

1140
00:55:58,355 --> 00:56:01,183
[thoughtful music]

1141
00:56:01,227 --> 00:56:03,229
[sighs]

1142
00:56:04,839 --> 00:56:08,060
I think you love hard.

1143
00:56:09,366 --> 00:56:11,629
And yes, it can come across
as overbearing.

1144
00:56:13,239 --> 00:56:15,676
I know where your heart is,
but sometimes I can imagine

1145
00:56:15,720 --> 00:56:17,330
it can be hard for others
to see.

1146
00:56:19,724 --> 00:56:21,726
Well I don't know any
other way to be.

1147
00:56:23,075 --> 00:56:25,251
Truth is, she's as independent
as you are.

1148
00:56:25,294 --> 00:56:27,732
So naturally she pulls
when you push.

1149
00:56:27,775 --> 00:56:30,474
Who died and made you the
relationship expert?

1150
00:56:30,517 --> 00:56:31,823
[chuckling]

1151
00:56:31,866 --> 00:56:33,409
I wouldn't say
I'm a relationship expert.

1152
00:56:33,433 --> 00:56:36,218
But, I'm pretty sure
I'm a Bonnie expert.

1153
00:56:36,262 --> 00:56:38,046
I'll give you that.

1154
00:56:38,090 --> 00:56:40,266
I just pushed really hard to
make this happen.

1155
00:56:40,309 --> 00:56:42,269
Well let's just say your
reputation's preceded you

1156
00:56:42,311 --> 00:56:43,704
and people are just afraid

1157
00:56:43,748 --> 00:56:46,446
to let you back on the same
stage together again.

1158
00:56:46,490 --> 00:56:48,206
Think about it, I literally
had to trick you

1159
00:56:48,230 --> 00:56:49,841
into performing with your
own daughter.

1160
00:56:49,884 --> 00:56:51,103
And vice versa.

1161
00:56:51,146 --> 00:56:52,583
You must see how ridiculous
that is.

1162
00:56:53,671 --> 00:56:55,542
I didn't ask you to do that.

1163
00:56:55,586 --> 00:56:57,109
Of course not.

1164
00:56:57,152 --> 00:56:59,067
You gals are the ones with
the talent.

1165
00:56:59,111 --> 00:57:01,809
I just wanted you to see how
special what you have is.

1166
00:57:01,853 --> 00:57:03,463
I don't need your help, Bret.

1167
00:57:03,507 --> 00:57:05,552
I didn't say you did, Bon.

1168
00:57:05,596 --> 00:57:09,251
[sighs] Is that why you came
over here tonight,

1169
00:57:09,295 --> 00:57:14,126
to let me know that this reunion
idea of yours

1170
00:57:14,169 --> 00:57:15,649
was like some sort of a favor?

1171
00:57:15,693 --> 00:57:18,217
Look, Bonnie, slow down.

1172
00:57:18,260 --> 00:57:19,740
I'm here because I wanna be.

1173
00:57:19,784 --> 00:57:23,222
Because this grand scheme of
yours has failed.

1174
00:57:23,265 --> 00:57:24,658
I kinda stuck my neck out here.

1175
00:57:24,702 --> 00:57:26,181
In more ways than one.

1176
00:57:27,531 --> 00:57:29,228
I didn't ask you to do that.

1177
00:57:30,664 --> 00:57:33,493
I learned a long, long time ago

1178
00:57:33,537 --> 00:57:37,671
that the only person that I
can rely on is myself.

1179
00:57:39,238 --> 00:57:42,720
Bonnie Rose, I've known you
for 22 years.

1180
00:57:42,763 --> 00:57:43,764
22.

1181
00:57:44,983 --> 00:57:46,177
And I've done everything
I can to show you

1182
00:57:46,201 --> 00:57:47,986
how important you are to me.

1183
00:57:48,029 --> 00:57:51,206
Now you tell me one time,
just one when I've let you down.

1184
00:57:56,298 --> 00:57:57,343
Right.

1185
00:58:00,346 --> 00:58:01,347
Goodnight Bonnie.

1186
00:58:22,020 --> 00:58:23,500
[sighs]

1187
00:58:23,543 --> 00:58:24,979
Nice job, Ashlyn.

1188
00:58:36,600 --> 00:58:37,601
Hmm.

1189
00:58:43,432 --> 00:58:44,695
♪ Holy infant

1190
00:58:44,738 --> 00:58:47,872
♪ So tender and mild

1191
00:58:48,873 --> 00:58:50,091
Bonnie.

1192
00:58:50,135 --> 00:58:52,398
I'm not here to argue or
cause trouble.

1193
00:58:52,441 --> 00:58:54,574
We're all professionals.

1194
00:58:54,618 --> 00:58:55,618
Okay.

1195
00:58:56,402 --> 00:58:57,795
There's a lot of work
to be done.

1196
00:58:57,838 --> 00:58:59,337
And there are a lotta butts
on the line,

1197
00:58:59,361 --> 00:59:01,276
not just mine and Ashlyn's.

1198
00:59:02,321 --> 00:59:03,365
I know.

1199
00:59:05,106 --> 00:59:06,107
Okay, good.

1200
00:59:06,891 --> 00:59:10,416
So, what do you have in mind?

1201
00:59:10,459 --> 00:59:12,461
I was thinking that maybe
I could come in

1202
00:59:12,505 --> 00:59:15,595
and record my part and then
Ashlyn could come in

1203
00:59:15,639 --> 00:59:17,466
and record hers and
then we could,

1204
00:59:17,510 --> 00:59:21,383
you know get this done without
all the contention.

1205
00:59:21,427 --> 00:59:22,863
Let me take a look at the song

1206
00:59:22,907 --> 00:59:25,257
and I'll see what I can do in
the timeframe we have.

1207
00:59:25,300 --> 00:59:29,130
Well, we don't necessarily
have a song.

1208
00:59:30,828 --> 00:59:31,829
Of course you don't.

1209
00:59:33,047 --> 00:59:34,745
What's that supposed to mean?

1210
00:59:34,788 --> 00:59:36,355
Well because that would require

1211
00:59:36,398 --> 00:59:38,638
the both of you working together
for more than a day or two.

1212
00:59:38,662 --> 00:59:42,274
Which in hindsight,
seems impossible.

1213
00:59:43,362 --> 00:59:45,364
[sighs]

1214
00:59:46,626 --> 00:59:49,934
♪ Holy infant

1215
00:59:49,977 --> 00:59:52,806
♪ So tender and mild

1216
00:59:52,850 --> 00:59:55,461
[playful music]

1217
01:00:02,381 --> 01:00:04,296
Have a good day at
school, Riley!

1218
01:00:07,995 --> 01:00:10,998
[sighs]
[phone dings]

1219
01:00:14,219 --> 01:00:16,221
[sighs]

1220
01:00:17,875 --> 01:00:19,659
[happy music]

1221
01:00:19,703 --> 01:00:20,704
Now we wait.

1222
01:00:48,122 --> 01:00:50,124
- Hi.
- Hey.

1223
01:00:51,560 --> 01:00:54,346
I wanted to apologize.

1224
01:00:54,389 --> 01:00:55,390
I'm...

1225
01:00:57,741 --> 01:00:59,351
I'm sorry.

1226
01:00:59,394 --> 01:01:04,095
I overreacted yesterday and
things got a little outta hand.

1227
01:01:04,965 --> 01:01:05,966
I'm embarrassed about it.

1228
01:01:09,056 --> 01:01:10,362
Hello Mother.

1229
01:01:10,405 --> 01:01:11,406
BONNIE: Ashlyn.

1230
01:01:12,538 --> 01:01:14,409
ASHLYN: Could you give
us a second?

1231
01:01:14,453 --> 01:01:15,454
Oh, sure.

1232
01:01:15,497 --> 01:01:17,021
It's okay.

1233
01:01:17,064 --> 01:01:19,458
We're all professionals and
we're here to record a song.

1234
01:01:19,501 --> 01:01:20,502
Right?

1235
01:01:21,460 --> 01:01:22,417
Right.

1236
01:01:22,461 --> 01:01:23,462
Absolutely.

1237
01:01:24,898 --> 01:01:29,424
So, you both ready to record the
song you don't have?

1238
01:01:30,643 --> 01:01:34,299
Well I was hoping that maybe
we could use

1239
01:01:34,342 --> 01:01:37,519
the melody from that song that
you played last time.

1240
01:01:37,563 --> 01:01:38,564
If that's okay with you.

1241
01:01:39,783 --> 01:01:40,740
Sure.

1242
01:01:40,784 --> 01:01:41,741
We can do that.

1243
01:01:41,785 --> 01:01:43,003
Okay.

1244
01:01:43,047 --> 01:01:46,659
And Ash... Lyn, Ashlyn,

1245
01:01:48,487 --> 01:01:51,490
well you've always been so great
with your poetic lyrics,

1246
01:01:52,752 --> 01:01:55,407
maybe we could start with that.

1247
01:01:55,450 --> 01:01:58,758
Sure, I've got the beginning of
something we can use.

1248
01:01:58,802 --> 01:02:00,151
- Okay.
- Okay.

1249
01:02:00,194 --> 01:02:02,414
I'll lay it down,
play it in the booth for you.

1250
01:02:04,503 --> 01:02:05,504
Thank you.

1251
01:02:10,639 --> 01:02:11,597
[Clears throat]
So.

1252
01:02:11,640 --> 01:02:14,034
[playful music]

1253
01:02:14,078 --> 01:02:15,079
Well I'll umm...

1254
01:02:22,608 --> 01:02:25,219
[happy music]

1255
01:02:31,530 --> 01:02:34,402
Wow, you really write small.

1256
01:02:35,534 --> 01:02:36,753
It's a small book, Mother.

1257
01:02:36,796 --> 01:02:39,538
Surely you can see it's
a small book.

1258
01:02:39,581 --> 01:02:40,626
Here it comes.

1259
01:02:47,241 --> 01:02:51,028
♪ The bells ring hear my
spirit sing ♪

1260
01:02:51,071 --> 01:02:55,554
♪ With this Christmas joy
you bring ♪

1261
01:02:55,597 --> 01:02:56,555
What?

1262
01:02:56,598 --> 01:02:57,556
Well it's really pretty.

1263
01:02:57,599 --> 01:02:58,557
It really, really is.

1264
01:02:58,600 --> 01:03:01,038
It just, it feels generic to me.

1265
01:03:01,081 --> 01:03:02,343
Ah, here we go.

1266
01:03:02,387 --> 01:03:04,041
Why don't you try that line
right there.

1267
01:03:05,651 --> 01:03:06,913
Would it matter if I said no?

1268
01:03:06,957 --> 01:03:08,959
What, you don't want my input
into our song?

1269
01:03:12,571 --> 01:03:17,794
♪ The snow, the lights,
the twinkle in your eyes ♪

1270
01:03:17,837 --> 01:03:18,795
No?

1271
01:03:18,838 --> 01:03:19,838
Okay.

1272
01:03:21,406 --> 01:03:25,584
♪ Here I am another Christmas,
another crazy Christmas ♪

1273
01:03:25,627 --> 01:03:29,544
♪ My mother's right,
no matter what ♪

1274
01:03:29,588 --> 01:03:32,983
♪ Dear Christmas why me

1275
01:03:34,680 --> 01:03:36,595
[Bonnie laughs]

1276
01:03:36,638 --> 01:03:41,121
♪ Here we are another Christmas
another crazy Christmas ♪

1277
01:03:41,165 --> 01:03:43,254
♪ My daughter's never wrong

1278
01:03:43,297 --> 01:03:47,736
♪ Not even for the sake of
a Christmas song ♪

1279
01:03:47,780 --> 01:03:52,132
♪ Why me

1280
01:03:52,176 --> 01:03:57,181
♪ I don't want to write
anymore ♪

1281
01:03:58,399 --> 01:04:01,925
♪ Look over there it's
the door ♪

1282
01:04:05,145 --> 01:04:06,494
You made me come here.

1283
01:04:06,538 --> 01:04:08,757
You're a grown woman, dear.

1284
01:04:10,194 --> 01:04:11,499
Maybe you both should go home

1285
01:04:11,543 --> 01:04:13,806
and write something real that
we can record.

1286
01:04:15,677 --> 01:04:17,592
So we can all fulfill our
contracts.

1287
01:04:19,464 --> 01:04:26,384
[Smith sighs]
Oh man.

1288
01:04:26,427 --> 01:04:29,735
Oh good, save me.

1289
01:04:29,778 --> 01:04:31,756
Got a text from Bonnie, she told
me she's gonna fix things

1290
01:04:31,780 --> 01:04:33,304
and get the last song recorded.

1291
01:04:33,347 --> 01:04:35,697
Oh, yeah.

1292
01:04:35,741 --> 01:04:37,569
They working on a song
right now?

1293
01:04:37,612 --> 01:04:39,571
They're laying something down.

1294
01:04:39,614 --> 01:04:40,920
Well, can I hear it?

1295
01:04:42,313 --> 01:04:43,314
Sure.

1296
01:04:44,576 --> 01:04:45,727
BONNIE: Why can't you
forgive me?

1297
01:04:45,751 --> 01:04:47,274
We will never agree.

1298
01:04:47,318 --> 01:04:50,538
That man, he took you
away from me.

1299
01:04:50,582 --> 01:04:52,801
At least I took a chance
on love.

1300
01:04:53,977 --> 01:04:57,023
Mom, you have had the same sweet
man knocking on your door

1301
01:04:57,067 --> 01:04:58,982
for 22 years.

1302
01:04:59,025 --> 01:05:01,462
I mean even for you that's sad.

1303
01:05:05,640 --> 01:05:06,772
I've heard enough.

1304
01:05:11,255 --> 01:05:13,779
[Bonnie sighs]

1305
01:05:16,347 --> 01:05:17,522
[Smith sighs]

1306
01:05:17,565 --> 01:05:20,046
ASHLYN: Guess they didn't like
our song.

1307
01:05:20,090 --> 01:05:21,091
Shocking.

1308
01:05:22,440 --> 01:05:24,921
[gentle music]

1309
01:05:41,285 --> 01:05:44,027
[Bonnie sighs]

1310
01:05:44,070 --> 01:05:47,856
♪ All is calm

1311
01:05:47,900 --> 01:05:51,556
♪ All is bright

1312
01:05:51,599 --> 01:05:54,472
♪ Round yon virgin

1313
01:05:54,515 --> 01:05:57,388
♪ Mother and child

1314
01:05:59,825 --> 01:06:01,218
I don't mean to bother you,

1315
01:06:01,261 --> 01:06:02,697
but are you Bonnie Rose?

1316
01:06:05,744 --> 01:06:07,789
I suppose I am.

1317
01:06:07,833 --> 01:06:10,357
Could you, would you mind

1318
01:06:10,401 --> 01:06:12,359
singing a Christmas carol
with us?

1319
01:06:13,578 --> 01:06:15,406
It would be a huge honor.

1320
01:06:21,673 --> 01:06:23,109
Can I make a deal with you?

1321
01:06:26,069 --> 01:06:27,418
Come on.

1322
01:06:27,461 --> 01:06:28,462
So.

1323
01:06:49,309 --> 01:06:52,182
["The First Noel"]

1324
01:07:00,320 --> 01:07:01,713
[chuckles]

1325
01:07:01,756 --> 01:07:06,761
♪ Born is the king of Israel

1326
01:07:08,763 --> 01:07:10,765
♪ Noel, Noel

1327
01:07:12,593 --> 01:07:17,120
♪ Noel, Noel

1328
01:07:17,163 --> 01:07:22,168
♪ Born is the king of Israel

1329
01:07:24,649 --> 01:07:26,955
♪ Noel, Noel

1330
01:07:28,696 --> 01:07:31,743
♪ Noel, Noel
-Grandma?

1331
01:07:33,440 --> 01:07:36,704
♪ Born is the king

1332
01:07:36,748 --> 01:07:40,360
♪ Of Israel

1333
01:07:41,927 --> 01:07:43,059
BONNIE: Thank you.

1334
01:07:43,102 --> 01:07:45,148
- Goodnight.
- Merry Christmas.

1335
01:07:45,191 --> 01:07:46,758
My mother.

1336
01:07:46,801 --> 01:07:48,412
Always a show stopper.

1337
01:07:49,239 --> 01:07:51,241
I never meant to make this the
Bonnie Rose show.

1338
01:07:52,198 --> 01:07:54,853
I'm sorry if I held you back.

1339
01:07:54,896 --> 01:07:56,724
It wasn't just you, Mom.

1340
01:07:56,768 --> 01:07:58,596
I just needed to fail on my own

1341
01:07:58,639 --> 01:08:00,424
